        -:   18:/** \class NoAlias
        -:   19:  * \ingroup Core_Module
        -:   20:  *
        -:   21:  * \brief Pseudo expression providing an operator = assuming no aliasing
        -:   22:  *
        -:   23:  * \tparam ExpressionType the type of the object on which to do the lazy assignment
        -:   24:  *
        -:   25:  * This class represents an expression with special assignment operators
        -:   26:  * assuming no aliasing between the target expression and the source expression.
        -:   27:  * More precisely it alloas to bypass the EvalBeforeAssignBit flag of the source expression.
        -:   28:  * It is the return type of MatrixBase::noalias()
        -:   29:  * and most of the time this is the only way it is used.
        -:   30:  *
        -:   31:  * \sa MatrixBase::noalias()
        -:   32:  */
